  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "The unit object I in a monoidal category is the object that acts as an identity for the tensor product: I ⊗ A ≅ A ≅ A ⊗ I for every object A, via coherent isomorphisms. It is the categorical analogue of the identity element in a monoid.\nIn the category of sets with Cartesian product, the unit object is any singleton set {∗}. In the category of vector spaces with tensor product, the unit is the base field. In the category of abelian groups with tensor product over ℤ, the unit is ℤ itself.\n",
  "name": "Unit Object",
